Provides a AWS Clean Rooms configured table. Configured tables are used to represent references to existing tables in the AWS Glue Data Catalog.

package main

import (
	"github.com/pulumi/pulumi-aws/sdk/v6/go/aws/cleanrooms"
	"github.com/pulumi/pulumi/sdk/v3/go/pulumi"
)

func main() {
	pulumi.Run(func(ctx *pulumi.Context) error {
		_, err := cleanrooms.NewConfiguredTable(ctx, "test_configured_table", &cleanrooms.ConfiguredTableArgs{
			Name:           pulumi.String("pulumi-example-table"),
			Description:    pulumi.String("I made this table with Pulumi!"),
			AnalysisMethod: pulumi.String("DIRECT_QUERY"),
			AllowedColumns: pulumi.StringArray{
				pulumi.String("column1"),
				pulumi.String("column2"),
				pulumi.String("column3"),
			},
			TableReference: &cleanrooms.ConfiguredTableTableReferenceArgs{
				DatabaseName: pulumi.String("example_database"),
				TableName:    pulumi.String("example_table"),
			},
			Tags: pulumi.StringMap{
				"Project": pulumi.String("Pulumi"),
			},
		})
		if err != nil {
			return err
		}
		return nil
	})
}

### Inputs

<pulumi-choosable type="language" values="python">

The ConfiguredTable resource accepts the following [input](/docs/intro/concepts/inputs-outputs) properties:



<div>
<pulumi-choosable type="language" values="csharp">
<dl class="resources-properties"><dt class="property-required property-replacement"
            title="Required">
        <span id="allowedcolumns_csharp">
<a data-swiftype-name="resource-property" data-swiftype-type="text" href="#allowedcolumns_csharp" style="color: inherit; text-decoration: inherit;">Allowed<wbr>Columns</a>
</span>
        <span class="property-indicator"></span>
        <span class="property-type">List&lt;string&gt;</span>
    </dt>
    <dd>The columns of the references table which will be included in the configured table.</dd><dt class="property-required"
            title="Required">
        <span id="analysismethod_csharp">
<a data-swiftype-name="resource-property" data-swiftype-type="text" href="#analysismethod_csharp" style="color: inherit; text-decoration: inherit;">Analysis<wbr>Method</a>
</span>
        <span class="property-indicator"></span>
        <span class="property-type">string</span>
    </dt>
    <dd>The analysis method for the configured table. The only valid value is currently <code>DIRECT_QUERY</code>.</dd><dt class="property-required property-replacement"
            title="Required">
        <span id="tablereference_csharp">
<a data-swiftype-name="resource-property" data-swiftype-type="text" href="#tablereference_csharp" style="color: inherit; text-decoration: inherit;">Table<wbr>Reference</a>
</span>
        <span class="property-indicator"></span>
        <span class="property-type"><a href="#configuredtabletablereference">Configured<wbr>Table<wbr>Table<wbr>Reference</a></span>
    </dt>
    <dd>A reference to the AWS Glue table which will be used to create the configured table.</p>
<ul>
<li><code>table_reference.database_name</code> - (Required - Forces new resource) - The name of the AWS Glue database which contains the table.</li>
<li><code>table_reference.table_name</code> - (Required - Forces new resource) - The name of the AWS Glue table which will be used to create the configured table.</li>
</ul></dd><dt class="property-optional"
            title="Optional">
        <span id="description_csharp">
<a data-swiftype-name="resource-property" data-swiftype-type="text" href="#description_csharp" style="color: inherit; text-decoration: inherit;">Description</a>
</span>
        <span class="property-indicator"></span>
        <span class="property-type">string</span>
    </dt>
    <dd>A description for the configured table.</dd><dt class="property-optional"
            title="Optional">
        <span id="name_csharp">
<a data-swiftype-name="resource-property" data-swiftype-type="text" href="#name_csharp" style="color: inherit; text-decoration: inherit;">Name</a>
</span>
        <span class="property-indicator"></span>
        <span class="property-type">string</span>
    </dt>
    <dd>The name of the configured table.</dd><dt class="property-optional"
            title="Optional">
        <span id="tags_csharp">

## Import



Using `pulumi import`, import `aws_cleanrooms_configured_table` using the `id`. For example:

```sh
$ pulumi import aws:cleanrooms/configuredTable:ConfiguredTable table 1234abcd-12ab-34cd-56ef-1234567890ab
```


To learn more about importing existing cloud resources, see [Importing resources](/docs/using-pulumi/adopting-pulumi/import/).
